title: Google’s Gemini and OpenAI’s ChatGPT go head-to-head in Cointelegraph test
description:
Comparisons of Google’s Gemini and OpenAI’s ChatGPT continue to flood internet social spaces, so we decided to put them to the test with questions of our own.

Earlier this week, Google launched its latest artificial intelligence (AI) model, Gemini, which it claimed to be the most advanced model currently available on the market, more so than the popular model developed by OpenAI GPT-4. 

This bold claim was treated like a challenge by community sleuths across the internet, who swiftly moved to examine the methods and benchmarks used by Google to assert supposed Gemini’s superiority, and poke fun at the company's marketing of the product.

David Gull, CEO of AI-powered wellness startup Vital, told Cointelegraph that each model, be it GPT-4, LLaMa, or now Gemini, has its own set of strengths and challenges.
